    "recap_headline": "University of North Carolina Ashville Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PLYMOUTH MEETING, Pa. -\nUNC Asheville Baseball fell in its middle game at Villanova on Saturday (Mar. 21) by a score of 10-4.\nThe teams traded scoreless frames for the first two innings, before Villanova scored four times in the third and once in the fourth for a 5-0 lead heading to the fifth. After a scoreless fifth, Asheville clawed back into the game with one run in the sixth and three in the seventh to cut the deficit to 5-4.\nBlaize Johnson\ndrove home the first run in the sixth on a single to center to score\nLogan Lowe\n, before the Bulldogs would get back in the game in the seventh.\nOwen Michelson\nled the inning off with a walk, before\nZeb Swangim\nripped a one-out single to right to move Michelson to third.\nColeman McGinnis\nwas hit by a pitch to load the bases, before Michelson scored on a\nLogan Lowe\ngroundout with the other two runners moving up 90 feet each. Johnson would drive in Swangim and McGinnis with a single to center to get the Bulldogs back within one. Villanova responded with three runs in the bottom of the seventh and two runs in the bottom of the eighth to bring the game to its final score.\nJohnson paced the offense with two hits and three RBI in the game, while\nPatrick Gillen\n, Michelson and Swangim each had one hit in the game. Lowe also drove in one run in the game. Lowe, Michelson, Swangim and McGinnis each scored once in the game. Michelson also stole one base in the game.\nCooper Smith\n(1-2) took the loss on the bump for the Bulldogs, allowing two runs on one hit through two innings with one walk and two strikeouts.\nNick Bruno\ncollected 0.2 innings of work allowing two runs on two hits with one walk, before passing the ball to\nGarrett Crum\nwho fired 3.2 innings of relief. Crum surrendered two runs, one earned on one hit with one walk and four strikeouts.\nMatthew Hall\nand\nLandon Gross\ncombined to finish the game, with Gross tossing a scoreless inning allowing two hits and picking up one strikeout.\nThe Bulldogs (12-11) come back tomorrow (Sunday, Mar. 22) to finish the series with Villanova. First pitch is set for 1:00 p.m., with\nvideo\nand\nlive stats\navailable at\nwww.uncabulldogs.com\n.",
